name: Consistent-Factor
description:
All updates have now moved to HuggingFace - https://huggingface.co/ConsistentFactor

Mage provides unlimited generations for my model with amazing features. They also share their revenue per content generation with me! Go check it out here: https://www.mage.space/

A merged model trying to get as close to realistic as I can.

V1 contained parts of Deliberate, URPM and Realistic Vision

V2 used updated Deliberate, Realistic Vision and URPM

V3 added RPG, HassanBlend, Dreamlike Diffusion, Babes (experiment 8), Experience (realistic), Protogen x5.3 and Protogen x5.8 to the original 3 models.

V3.2 used updated Realistic Vision, Experience and switched to Babes Experiment 9.

V4 has been redone from the ground up. The model will consist of Deliberate, Realistic Vision, Experience, RPG, Analog Madness and CyberRealistic. This will come in 3 flavours, Standard, LE edition and soon a vivid edition for those who like the bolder colours seen in V3.2.

Consistent Factor Euclid or V5 has been redone from the ground up...again to produce the most realistic and flexible model to date, I removed RPG and Deliberate and replaced them with 3 highly realistic models.

V5.1 updates the models used in V5 and adds 2 more to the mix to create what is the most realistic version yet.

Recommend: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras, Steps: 20+, Hires fix 0.15 - 0.2, CFG 6 - 8.

I would also recommend using epi_noiseoffset for V4 - https://civitai.com/models/13941?modelVersionId=16576

I would recommend using Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix for V5 - https://civitai.com/models/8765?modelVersionId=10638

modelVersions.name: Euclid (v5)
modelVersions.description:
Euclid or V5 has been redone from the ground up...again to produce the most realistic and flexible model to date, I removed RPG and Deliberate and replaced them with 3 highly realistic models.

Merge weights are as follows:
65% Cyberrealistic V2.1
35% Experience_realistic V2
20% RealisticVision V2
20% AnalogMadness V4
15% Secret model 1
15% Secret model 2
20% Secret model 3

The model is much more flexible than previous versions and no longer creates close-up/portraits 90% of the time, it's more like 60% - 70% now. It does seem less flexible with CFG though as (in testing) when creating the same image using CFG 6 it would more often than not create a very similar image on CFG 7, sometimes even CFG 7.5.

I recommend using Hires Fix if possible as it really brings out the detail, I usually use a denoise strength of 0.3 - 0.35.

I also use the SD Ultimate Upscaler at a denoise strength of 0.2 - 0.30.
